  "id": "019d32d8-0926-77b3-b66f-1e956cb858fb",
  "content": "# BM25Searcher + RRFusion -- Decision Record (2026-03-28)\n\n## What: Phase 2c of hybrid search pipeline. Store-agnostic BM25 searcher and reciprocal rank fusion.\n\n## Key Design Decisions:\n1. BM25Searcher normalizes scores via min-max on tier-weighted values BEFORE creating NormalizedScore. Raw BM25 scores are unbounded positive, so NormalizedScore::new() would clamp everything to 1.0 if applied to raw scores.\n2. RRFusion uses f64 for RRF accumulation to avoid precision loss when summing small 1/(k+rank) values across many searchers.\n3. RRFusion delegates to PassThrough for single-set input (avoids RRF rank-based scoring which is meaningless for a single set).\n4. Component scores store tier-weighted values (consistent with VectorSearcher) so downstream consumers can compare across searcher types.\n5. fetch_limit() helper extracted to shared function to prevent DRY violations as more searchers are added.\n\n## Review Findings Worth Remembering:\n- RRF k=0 breaks the smoothing property. Validated with debug_assert + runtime clamp to 1.\n- Three parallel HashMaps in fusion is a cache locality anti-pattern. Single Accumulator struct is better.\n- or_insert for component score merge silently drops higher scores. Use max-wins (and_modify + or_insert).\n\n## What Blocked:\n- NormalizedScore::new() clamping raw BM25 scores to 1.0. Required restructuring to normalize BEFORE wrapping in newtype.",
